    <!-- About Caesar Cipher Section -->
    <section id="about" class="fade-up my-16">
      <div class="glass-card p-6 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold border-l-4 border-cyan-400 pl-4 mb-6">📜 About Caesar Cipher</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div>
            <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed"><span class="font-bold text-cyan-300">What?</span> The Caesar cipher is one of the oldest known encryption techniques. Each letter in the plaintext is shifted a fixed number of positions down the alphabet.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-gray-200"><span class="font-bold text-green-300">History:</span> Used by Julius Caesar to protect military communications, shifting by 3 positions. Ancient cryptography at its finest!</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-gray-200"><span class="font-bold text-cyan-300">How it works:</span> Replace each letter with a letter a certain number of places away. Decryption reverses the shift.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-gray-200">Modern cryptography builds on these principles, but today’s ciphers are far more complex.</p>
          </div>
